an that consists of a conical snow-cloak made of straw. Generally, \'\'yukinko\'\' are depicted as small, elf-like creatures wearing \'\'yuki mino\'\'.\n\n====Name origin====\nSnorunt is a combination of \'\'snow\'\' and \'\'runt\'\' (a smaller-than-average animal).\n\nYukiwarashi may be a combination of 雪 \'\'yuki\'\' (snow) and 座敷童子 \'\'zashiki warashi\'\' (a spiritual creature found in the folklore of Iwate Prefecture). It should be noted that 童子 \'\'warashi\'\' on its own is simply an archaic word for child.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ice|type2=Ice\n|ja=ユキワラシ \'\'Yukiwarashi\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|雪 \'\'yuki\'\'|snow}} and {{tt|座敷童子 \'\'zashiki warashi\'\'|a spiritual creature found in the folklore of Iwate Prefecture}}\'\'\n|de=Schneppke|demeaning=From {{tt|\'\'Schnee\'\'|snow}} and {{tt|\'\'Steppke\'\'|little boy}}\n|fr=Stalgamin|frmeaning=From \'\'{{wp|stalagmite}}\'\' and {{tt|\'\'gamin\'\'|brat}}. A play on {{tt|\'\'sale gamin\'\'|dirty brat}}\n|es=Snorunt|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Snorunt|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=눈꼬마 \'\'Nunkoma\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|눈 \'\'nun\'\'|snow}} and {{tt|꼬마 \'\'kko\'ma\'\'|tiny person, small child}}\n|zh_cmn=雪童子 \'\'Xuě Tóng Zǐ\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From its Japanese name. 童子 may also be derived from 座敷童子 \'\'zashiki warashi\'\'. Literally "Snow boy/lad"\n|hi=स्नोरन्ट \'\'Snorunt\'\'|himeaning=Transliteration of English name}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Ash\'s Glalie|Ash\'s Snorunt]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ice|prevnum=360|prev=Wynaut|nextnum=362|next=Glalie}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Shadow Pokémon in Pokémon XD]]\n[[Category:Pokémon with cross-generational evolutions]]\n[[Category:Pokémon that evolve by evolutionary stone]]\n[[Category:Pokémon that evolve using Dawn Stone]]\n[[Category:Pokémon that evolve based on gender]]\n\n[[de:Schneppke]]\n[[es:Snorunt]]\n[[fr:Stalgami